  "description": "Something calls forth a bravery you didn't know you possessed.",
  "content": "The moment demands more than you thought you could give. Someone needs protection. A principle needs defending. A fear needs facing. Your usual caution says to retreat, to let someone else handle it, to protect yourself. But something deeper rises up—a refusal to be ruled by fear, a commitment to something beyond self-preservation. Your hands might be shaking, but you step forward anyway. This is what courage actually feels like: not the absence of fear, but action despite it.",
